name: potato production | potato | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/2420/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of potatoes (fresh matter). The yield is 41001 kg/ha at a moisture content at storage of 78%.

This activity starts after the harvest of the previous crop. The inputs of seeds, mineral fertilisers, pesticides and irrigation water are considered. It is assumed that no organic fertilisers are applied.


The dataset includes all machine operations and corresponding machine infrastructure and sheds. Machine operations are: soil cultivation, sowing, fertilisation, irrigation, weed control, pest and pathogen control, harvest, transport from field to farm (1 km) and grading of potatoes. Further, direct field emissions are included. This activity ends after harvest and drying of grains at the farm gate.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/011:Growing of non-perennial crops/0113:Growing of vegetables and melons, roots and tubers

processDocumentation.timeDescription: The yield data have been collected for the years 2001-2006.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Conventional production typical for the country. Water for irrigation is pumped from 48 meter depth by electric pumps.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography US. If the dataset is used for other countries, particular care must be taken to the pesticides used, as there might be pesticides that are not allowed in a particular country.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data come from the NREL database and from varoius U.S database. Data were compiled from statistics, literature, farm survey reports, documents from extension services, and expert knowledge.
